As shooting for ‘Mokalik’, a new film by awards-winning filmmaker, Kunle Afolayan begins today August 29, 2018, the cast converged at the Golden Effects office, Ikeja, Lagos yesterday for the reading of the script.  Photos show singer Simi, Femi Adebayo, Lateef Oladimeji and comic actors like Wale Akorede (Okunu), Ayo Ogunshina (Papa Lolo) and Dayo Akinpelu (Alabi Yellow) during the session.  The single-location shoot, according to the awards-winning film director will tell the story of the protagonist in a space of 12 hours, detailing some of the intriguing occurrences in a typical mechanic workshop. 